{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fix Generator to include classes in static initializers",
    "body": "This commit fixes the Generator class to include classes instead of packages in the static initializers. The method genPreambleStaticInitializers() now correctly generates the static initializers for the JSP page, including the classes. The change does not affect the reason why the method is provided or the usage of the method, but it affects the logic of the function. The pre-conditions and post-conditions of the method remain the same."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Exit non-blocking write loop when write buffer is full",
    "body": "This commit fixes the SocketWrapperBase's writeNonBlocking method to exit the loop earlier when the write buffer is full and no more data can be written. The changes will affect the behavior of the method, potentially leading to incomplete writes. The method will no longer attempt to write more data when the write buffer is full, as indicated by the comment 'Therefore the write buffer will still be full. Nothing else to do here. Exit the loop.'"
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update DEFAULT_CIPHERS constant",
    "body": "The DEFAULT_CIPHERS constant in AbstractEndpoint.java has been updated to include !kRSA. This change enhances the security of the Tomcat server by adding support for RSA ciphers."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fix hostname verifier class name usage in JNDIRealm",
    "body": "This commit fixes the usage of the hostname verifier class name in JNDIRealm. The method setHostnameVerifierClassName now uses the provided verifierClassName instead of hostNameVerifierClassName. This change ensures that the correct class name is used for SSL connections."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Report failed and slow queries conditionally to JMX",
    "body": "This commit refactors the reportFailedQuery and reportSlowQuery methods in SlowQueryReportJmx to conditionally notify JMX of failed and slow queries based on the isLogFailed() and isLogSlow() methods. The methods will only send notifications to JMX if the respective log methods return true. This change aims to improve the logging and reporting of queries in a JMX-enabled database."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Improve HTTP/2 test case for window size and settings frame",
    "body": "This commit enhances the test case for HTTP/2 protocol by adding scenarios for further reducing and increasing the window size. The test method now covers additional scenarios where the stream 3 window becomes negative and the window size is increased after being reduced. The changes improve the robustness of the test case and provide more comprehensive testing for the HTTP/2 protocol."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Fixed socket wrapper flush after writing window update frames",
    "body": "This commit fixes the socket wrapper flush after writing window update frames in the Http2UpgradeHandler class. The changes ensure that the socket wrapper is properly flushed after writing window update frames, which improves the overall performance and reliability of the WebSocket connection."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update last read/write timestamps in NioEndpoint",
    "body": "This commit updates the last read and write timestamps in NioEndpoint to improve the handling of read and write operations. The changes ensure that the timestamps are updated correctly after the read and write operations are completed, which may affect the behavior of the method in certain scenarios."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update testGetURLs method to use 'war' protocol",
    "body": "This commit fixes the testGetURLs method to correctly test the getURLs method of a URLClassLoader in a tomcat context. The method now expects URLs in the 'war' protocol instead of 'jar' protocol. The test remains the same, but the expected URLs have been updated to reflect the change in protocol. The class loader is now loaded and initialized with a custom class loader to load classes from a specific directory."
}

{
    "type": "feat",
    "subject": "Introduce configureDataSource method for BasicDataSourceFactory",
    "body": "This commit introduces a new method configureDataSource in BasicDataSourceFactory, which allows for configuring a BasicDataSource instance based on given properties. The method is used to set various properties such as defaultAutoCommit, defaultReadOnly, and defaultTransactionIsolation. The createDataSource method has been refactored to use the new configureDataSource method."
}

{
    "type": "fix",
    "subject": "Update JvmRouteBinderValve documentation",
    "body": "The documentation for JvmRouteBinderValve has been updated to reflect the correct configuration method. The Valve is now added to the cluster definition at conf/server.xml instead of the host definition. This change aims to improve the clarity and consistency of the documentation."
}

